column1: # Name: Mean age at first birth

# Definition: The mean age at first birth is the mean age of mothers at the birth of their first child if women were subject throughout their lives to the age-specific fertility rates of first order births in a given year.
# Source: United Nations, World Fertility Report, 2012
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
